<subSubSection id="C340655EB709B11CFF1BFEA4FA8BFE4D" box="[199,1405,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE536D5B709B11CFF1BFEA4FA8BFE4D" blockId="6.[151,1436,153,468]" box="[199,1405,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC7B709B11CFF1BFEA4FEB8FE4D" bold="true" box="[199,334,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">Etymology.</emphasis>
We name this species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D56B709B11CFD97FEA7FD3CFE4D" authorityName="Pessacq &amp; Rivera-Pomar" authorityYear="2019" box="[587,714,370,395]" class="Insecta" family="Gripopterygidae" genus="Andiperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morenensis">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC7B709B11CFD97FEA7FD3CFE4D" box="[587,714,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">morenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in reference to its 
<typeStatus id="54E18877B709B11CFC7EFEA4FC24FE4D" box="[930,978,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="257">type</typeStatus>
locality, the “Perito Moreno” Glacier.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
